Cell.Data: U.S. Office of the National Coordinator (ONC)
Sets expectations for data elements registered or used as part of the structured data capture project
A code that defines the data element in terms of SDC's data element concept value set.
For SDC conformance, if there is no class-property mapping, then at least one of the 'code' repetitions SHALL come from the "DataElement SDC Concept" value set (which is extensible)
A mapping that defines the data element in terms of the SDC project's ObjectClass and Property value sets.
This should be expressed as "[uri for object class code system]#[code for object class code system] | [uri for property code system]#[code for property code system]"
We express the mapping even though the class and property extensions already convey the data to ensure that systems that don't recognize the extensions still understand the mappings
Property extension can only be specified if ObjectClass extension is present
Must have either a code or an object-property mapping from the SDC value set
Allowed values for the ISO 11179 ObjectClass extension when used for Structured Data Capture purposes
Allowed values for the ISO 11179 ObjectClass Property extension when used for Structured Data Capture purposes
Codes that can be used to identify the data element concept for this data element for Structured Data Capture purposes
